Ahead of the Republic Day, India will get its largest Tricolour, 66 feet high and 99 feet wide, to be hoisted on a 293 feet tall pole in Ranchi.To be hoisted by Defence Minister Manohar Parrikar on January 23, the flag will be taller than the Qutub Minar.The event will coincide with the birth anniversary of Netaji Subhas Chandra Bose.The flag has been created by 120 workers engaged in two shifts for the last 40 days and the cost of the project is estimated to be around Rs 1.25 crore, State government sources said.Currently, the worldâ€™s largest and tallest Tricolour of 96/64 feet in dimension was hoisted on a 250 feet high pole in Faridabad last year. -- PTI